The paper deals with distributed computation of eigenvalues of a sample covariance matrix over a wireless network, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithms are based on consensus steps, which are commonly used in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses applications to spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
